Name:Conditional

Categories: Language

Related:

Synopsis: ( BoolExp ) ? NumExp1 : NumExp2

Description: If the value of $BoolExp$ is <tt>true</tt> then the value of $NumExp1$ else the value of $NumExp2$.

Examples:
<screen>
(3 > 2) ? 10 : 20
(3 > 20) ? 10 : 20
</screen>

